<item>
            <title>[LU-13726] checkpatch.pl print empty correction string if mistake string have &apos;(&apos; </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13726</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;checkpatch.pl print empty correction string if mistake string have &apos;(&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These input (mistake string) prints empty correction string.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ERR_PTR&amp;#40;PTR_ERR||ERR_CAST&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ERR_PTR.PTR_ERR||ERR_CAST&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Error Eg:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;CHECK: &apos;ERR_PTR(PTR_ERR(&apos; may be misspelled - perhaps &apos;&apos;?
#185: FILE: ./lustre/mdt/mdt_identity.c:185:
+ return ERR_PTR(PTR_ERR(entry));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the &lt;tt&gt;typo_fix&lt;/tt&gt; is a matched regexp, then the checked string will not be found in &lt;tt&gt;spelling_fix&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; may be misspelled - perhaps &apos;CHECKPATCH ERROR&apos;?
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
